'README.md': [
'# Novelty Catcher Agent',
'',
'**DACTA SIEMLess Platform** — Security log anomaly detection agent.',
'',
'## Quick Start',
'',
'```bash',
'# 1. Install dependencies',
'pip install -r requirements.txt',
'',
'# 2. Set environment variables',
'export ELASTIC_URL="https://your-es-cluster:9200"',
'export ELASTIC_API_KEY="your-api-key"',
'',
'# 3. Edit config.yaml (set agent name, org, indices, etc.)',
'',
'# 4. Learn from historical data (first run)',
'python main.py -c config.yaml -m learn-from-elastic --learn-hours 168',
'',
'# 5. Start monitoring',
'python main.py -c config.yaml -m monitor',
'```',
'',
'## Modes',
'',
'| Mode | Description |',
'|------|-------------|',
'| `monitor` | Poll Elasticsearch, score events, report alerts |',
'| `learn-from-elastic` | Fetch historical data, train Isolation Forest baseline |',
'',
'## Architecture',
'',
'```',
'Elasticsearch  --->  [Elastic Client]  --->  [Detector]  --->  [Reporter]  --->  SIEMLess API',
'                     poll / fetch            score events       heartbeat         /api/novelty-catcher',
'                                             train model        alerts',
'                                                                config pull',
'```',
'',
'## Files',
'',
'| File | Purpose |',
'|------|---------|',
'| `main.py` | Entry point, CLI, config loading, orchestration |',
'| `elastic_client.py` | Elasticsearch REST client (no SDK dependency) |',
'| `detector.py` | Isolation Forest novelty detection engine |',
'| `reporter.py` | SIEMLess API client (heartbeat, alerts, config) |',
'| `config.yaml` | Agent configuration (env vars supported via `${VAR}`) |',
'| `requirements.txt` | Python package dependencies |',
'',
'## API Endpoints',
'',
'Base: `https://dacta-siemless.vercel.app/api/novelty-catcher`',
'',
'| Action | Method | Query Param |',
'|--------|--------|-------------|',
'| Heartbeat | POST | `?action=heartbeat` |',
'| Alert | POST | `?action=alert` |',
'| Pull Config | GET | `?action=config&catcher_id=<id>` |',
'| Feature Schema | GET | `?action=feature_schema&org_id=<id>` |',
'',
'## State Directory',
'',
'The `./state` directory stores:',
'- `model.pkl` — Trained Isolation Forest model',
'- `model_meta.json` — Category maps, known sources, field config',
'- `catcher_id.txt` — Persisted catcher ID',
].join('\n'),

